cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.CE 

Reasoning: 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on studying the rate perspective of a communication setup subject to beamforming and power constraints. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is also likely as the paper deals with a two-tier network and proposes a scheme based on physical-layer network coding and compute-and-forward. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possible category as the paper discusses the design of beamformers and power allocation, which are related to control and optimization. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper deals with communication between mobile users and a basestation. 
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) is also a less likely category, but the paper does involve computational methods for solving the beamformer design and power allocation problem.
